Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and sentence classification task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper compares the performance of different RNN architectures using LSTMs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with neural networks and their performance on a specific task. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper focuses on the performance of LSTM-based RNNs. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the architecture of neural networks and their performance on a specific task, which can be relevant to computer vision tasks as well.
